  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best TED Talks by youth?",
  "response": "There are several impactful TED Talks delivered by youth that have resonated with audiences around the world. Here are some of the best TED Talks by young speakers:\n\n1. **\"What adults can learn from kids\" by Adora Svitak**\n   - In this talk, Adora, a child prodigy, shares her insights on how children can teach adults about creativity, passion, and the importance of listening to the younger generation.\n\n2. **\"The danger of a single story\" by Chimamanda Ngozi Adichie**\n   - Although she is known for her literary career, Adichie delivered this talk when she was relatively young. She discusses how stereotypes are formed and the importance of hearing multiple perspectives.\n\n3. **\"How to make stress your friend\" by Kelly McGonigal**\n   - While not a teenager at the time, Kelly was still in her early career when delivering this talk. She explores the unexpected ways stress can be beneficial and offers practical advice for managing it.\n\n4. **\"Your body language may shape who you are\" by Amy Cuddy**\n   - In this influential talk, Cuddy discusses how body language affects how others see us and how we see ourselves, fostering a discussion about confidence and self-perception.\n\n5. **\"I am not your princess\" by 13-year-old Tavi Gevinson**\n   - In this powerful talk, Tavi challenges stereotypes about young women and explores the complexities of growing up, identity, and the pressures faced by youth today.\n\n6. **\"The power of vulnerability\" by Bren\u00e9 Brown**\n   - Although Bren\u00e9 Brown is not a youth speaker per se, her work on vulnerability resonates strongly with younger audiences and speaks to the experiences of youth today.\n\n7. **\"This is what hate feels like\" by Ashten T. Jude**\n   - A courageous talk by a young voice addressing personal experiences with hate and discrimination, urging listeners to stand against intolerance and promote empathy.\n\n8. **\"What I learned from going blind in my 20s\" by Laura Becker**\n   - Laura Becker shares her inspiring journey of navigating life after losing her sight, emphasizing the importance of resilience and redefining possibilities.\n\nThese TED Talks showcase the diverse perspectives and experiences of young speakers, offering valuable lessons and insights on various topics.",
